WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000
Digital Tale of Genji - Feature Introduction.

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:05.500
We will explain the Patapata Face Comparison.

00:00:05.500 --> 00:00:08.000
A tool to easily compare Genji Hyakunin Isshu editions that look identical at first glance.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:10.000
For example, you can see the difference between closed eyes and open eyes.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:13.500
You can confirm differences in character faces using the image comparison tool.

00:00:13.500 --> 00:00:15.500
It uses vdiff.js.

00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:17.000
Published by the ROIS-DS Center for Open Data in the Humanities.

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:20.000
About the origin of the name "Patapata Face Comparison."

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:23.000
The motion resembles aori proofreading, where manuscripts are overlaid and flipped quickly.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:25.000
Please also refer to "About this page" for details.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Access it from the menu screen.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:30.000
Select "Genji Hyakunin Isshu" under "Comparison of Illustration Images."

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:33.000
Launch the image comparison tool.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:35.000
Click the "Compare (vdiff.js)" button.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:39.000
How to operate the image comparison tool.

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:42.000
Move the dividing line left and right on the image.

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:45.000
You can dynamically confirm the differing parts of the two images.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:50.000
Move the dividing line to check the differences.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:55.000
Here is a comparison example.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:58.000
Even back views that look identical have differences.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:00.000
The two editions are displayed side by side.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:03.000
Using patapata reveals a very slight difference in part of the hair.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:07.000
Even the smallest differences can be confirmed.

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:10.000
Zoom in to examine the differences.

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:14.000
Here are some additional features.

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:17.000
The highlight display feature.

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:19.500
Only the differing parts of the two images are emphasized with highlighting.

00:01:19.500 --> 00:01:21.000
Noise from differences in photography conditions is mechanically removed.

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:24.000
The red-blue display feature.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:27.000
Differing parts of images are displayed in red and blue.

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:30.000
Since noise removal is not performed, original differences can be confirmed.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:33.000
Digital Tale of Genji.

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:36.000
Thank you for watching.
